      "message": "I expected this to be a union type, since it is a specific type in the Go code.\n\nLook at Perf for example:\n\n   https://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/refs/heads/main/perf/go/ts/main.go#92\n   \nWhere AllStepDetection is defined as:\n\nhttps://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/refs/heads/main/perf/go/types/types.go#126\n\nAnd that appears as a union type in json/index.ts:\n\nhttps://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/refs/heads/main/perf/modules/json/index.ts#286\n\nThen, I created a Record\u003c\u003e that maps those types to the display values:\n\nhttps://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/refs/heads/main/perf/modules/cluster-summary2-sk/cluster-summary2-sk.ts#94\n\nThe nice part is when I add a new type of StepDetection the TS will fail to compile until I add the new value to the Record\u003c\u003e, so I know they are always in sync.",
